### Exercise 4.6 async clone route checks

### Step 1: create a base entry
POST http://localhost:3000/entries/new
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

content=Original+entry+for+clone

### Step 2: clone the entry
POST http://localhost:3000/entries/1/clone

### Step 3: verify the cloned entry exists (should be id 2)
GET http://localhost:3000/entries/2

### Step 4: clone a missing entry (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:3000/entries/999/clone

### Optional: to trigger 400 for invalid content, create a very long entry
### (length >= 4994) and then clone it to exceed the 5000 char limit.
